cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically the Semantic Role Labelling (SRL) task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses a state-of-the-art neural ELMo-based SRL sequence labelling model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with using external syntactic information to improve NLP tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses a neural network model for SRL. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with encoding syntactic parses and injecting them into a model, which could be seen as a form of feature engineering similar to computer vision tasks.
